spec: multiprocessing_extra142
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(multiprocessing)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html — Python multiprocessing documentation"
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html#multiprocessing.Process — Process documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/multiprocessing/process.py, Lib/multiprocessing/context.py"
  notes:
    - "This spec covers: multiprocessing.Process — __name__=='Process' (len=7); __module__=='multiprocessing.context' (len=23); __doc__==None (no docstring). multiprocessing.Process.__init__ — __qualname__=='BaseProcess.__init__' (len=20); co_argcount==6 ('self','group','target','name','args','kwargs'); co_varnames.__len__()==8 (includes 'daemon' and 'count' as additional locals). multiprocessing.Process.start — __qualname__=='BaseProcess.start' (len=17); __doc__=='\\nStart child process\\n' (len=21); co_argcount==1. multiprocessing.Process.join — __qualname__=='BaseProcess.join' (len=16); __doc__=='\\nWait until child process terminates\\n' (len=37); co_argcount==2; co_varnames.__len__()==3. multiprocessing.Process.terminate — __qualname__=='BaseProcess.terminate' (len=21); __doc__ len==68; co_argcount==1. multiprocessing.Process.is_alive — __qualname__=='BaseProcess.is_alive' (len=20); __doc__ len==33; co_argcount==1. multiprocessing.Process.kill — __qualname__=='BaseProcess.kill' (len=16); __doc__ len==68. All verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "multiprocessing.Process.__qualname__=='Process' (len=7) and __module__=='multiprocessing.context' (len=23) because Process is a context-specific subclass of BaseProcess; all method qualnames show 'BaseProcess.<method>' revealing the MRO. Process.__init__ co_argcount==6 (the richest parameter list in this spec: self, group, target, name, args, kwargs); co_varnames.__len__()==8 adds 'daemon' and 'count'. terminate and kill both have __doc__.__len__()==68 — same length for symmetric SIGTERM/SIGKILL docs. start and kill both have qualname len==16 (the shortest method qualnames in this spec, tied); terminate and is_alive both have qualname len==20 (tied for second-longest). All verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
  created_at: "2026-04-11T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

